text: Notch shows interest in adding wood.
Oak wood is currently one of the first blocks in Minecraft.
The texture of wood has been changed.
Showed that breaking wood now drops 3–5 wooden planks.
The above changed of breaking wood dropping 3-5 wooden planks has been implemented.[needs testing]
Breaking wood now gives the block instead of wooden planks.
Wood can now be destroyed only by fire if it had several sides simultaneously burning. If only one side was burning, the fire and wood block lasts forever.
Wood can now be smelted into charcoal.
Wood and wooden planks now burn and are destroyed if any one of the sides are lit on fire.
With the addition of birch and spruce saplings, their respective wood types have now become renewable resources.
Added "Getting Wood" achievement for picking up a wood item.
Oak wood now generates in villages.
Different types of wood now produce different colors of planks when crafted.
Oak wood is now found in the new bonus chests.
Each type of wood now has a unique name.
All types of blocks of wood are now rotatable, with the wood placed with the inner side facing the player (similarly to pistons).
Large oak trees now generate with horizontal wood blocks.
Wood blocks now have new sounds when being walked on and broken.
The orientation of placed wood blocks is now determined by which face of another block they are placed against, similarly to levers.
Oak wood now generates as part of witch huts.
As a feature of resource packs, each wood block has its own top, meaning that wood tops can now be colored separately.
Added acacia and roofed oak wood.
"Roofed Oak" has been renamed to "Dark Oak Wood".
The textures of acacia and dark oak wood have been changed.
The top texture of all blocks of wood now have unique textures, rather than sharing it with oak.
Wood in bonus chests may now also be acacia.
Wood found in bonus chests can now may be of any type, rather than just acacia or oak.
Bonus chests now have less wood.
Added taiga villages, which generates with spruce wood.
Savanna villages now generate with acacia wood.
Oak and dark oak wood now generate in woodland mansions.
Logs now generate as part of the newly added shipwrecks.
The side texture for stripped jungle logs has been changed.
Jeb tweets an image of new textures for iron blocks, obsidian and birch logs.
Jeb reppears with an image of all the new log textures.
JAPPA tweets an image of a less-blurry birch texture.
JAPPA tweets an image of new crafting table, wood planks and wood textures.
The textures of logs has been changed.
The textures of logs has been changed again.
Dark oak logs now generate as part of the new pillager outposts.
The top textures of logs has been changed.
The top textures of stripped logs has been changed.
Stripped oak logs and wood now generate in the updated plains villages.
Stripped spruce logs and wood now generate in the new snowy tundra villages.
Stripped logs now generate in the updated savanna villages.
Spruce logs can now be found in chests in taiga village houses.
Logs can now be used to craft a smoker.
The top textures of normal and stripped jungle logs have been changed, once again.
Stripped logs and logs can now be used to craft campfires.
Crimson and Warped logs were shown as part of crimson forest and warped forest biome.
Added regular and stripped crimson and warped stems.
The top textures of stripped crimson and warped stems have been changed.
Duplicate and unused textures for stripped warped stems have been removed.
Oak log can now generate in the mineshafts instead of oak wood.
Mangrove Logs were shown on Minecraft Live 2021.
Changed crimson and warped stems textures to match Bedrock Edition.
The top texture of dark oak log has been changed.
The side textures of stripped dark oak log has been changed, to match the color of its top texture.
32px Textures of stripped dark oak log has been changed again.
Added oak, spruce and birch wood. Spruce and birch wood are not available in the inventory.
Added spruce and birch wood to the inventory.
Removed oak wood from the inventory.
Oak trees now generate with spruce wood instead of oak wood.
Re-added oak wood to the creative inventory.
Oak trees once again generate with oak wood, making it obtainable in Survival mode.
Added jungle wood to the creative inventory.
All types of blocks of wood are now rotatable, with the wood placed with the inner side facing the player (similarly to pistons).
Added acacia and dark oak wood.
The texture of wood tops have been their own unique texture for each type of wood.
Oak wood now generates naturally in plains and savanna villages.
The tooltip has been changed from [woodtype] Wood to [woodtype] Log.
The tooltip has been changed from [woodtype] Log to [woodtype] Wood.
Spruce wood now generates in witch huts.
Savanna villages now generate using acacia wood, which previously used oak wood.
Spruce wood now generates in taiga and ice plains villages.
Oak and dark oak wood now generate in woodland mansions.
Wood can now be found inside bonus chests.
Woodland mansions now have birch wood instead of oak wood.
Added stripped logs as part of Experimental Gameplay.
Stripped logs have been fully implemented.
As an exclusive feature, oak, spruce and dark oak stripped logs now generate as part of shipwrecks.
The side textures for stripped jungle wood has been changed.
The top textures of stripped spruce and stripped dark oak logs have been changed.
The textures of logs have been changed.
The top textures of stripped logs have been changed.
"Wood" and "Stripped Wood" have been renamed to "Log" and "Stripped Log".
Logs are now used to craft wood, campfires, and smokers.
Stripped spruce, oak, and acacia logs now generate in new villages.
Dark oak logs now generate in pillager outpost watchtowers and as a pile of logs.
Dark oak logs can now be found in pillager outpost chests.
Spruce logs can now be found in taiga and snowy taiga village house chests.
Added regular and stripped crimson and warped stems.
Added oak, spruce, and birch wood.
Spruce wood and birch wood can now be crafted into spruce and birch wood planks, stairs and slabs.
All types of blocks of wood are now rotatable, with the wood placed with the inner side facing the player (similarly to pistons).
Prior to this update, in PlayStation 3 Edition, wood with special data values looked like it is in Java Edition only in the inventory or when held, and when placed looked completely different.

Prior to this version, in Xbox 360 Edition, higher data values of wood would result in blocks that had the inside texture facing along the expected axis, but the bark textures not rotated. These data values would function like their own blocks and would not change orientation depending on the targeted block face.
The textures of birch and jungle wood have been changed.
Added acacia and dark oak wood. It can only be obtained by modding the game.
Acacia and dark oak wood is now obtainable through the creative inventory.
Acacia and dark oak wood is now obtainable in survival.
The textures of logs have been changed.
The top textures of stripped logs have been changed.

minecraft:log2 blocks with numerical metadata variants 2-3, 6-7, 10-11 and 14-15, which are inaccessible through normal gameplay, now have no model rather than appearing identical to either acacia or dark oak wood.

Logs are now defined via block states rather than by numerical metadata. Prior to this version, the numerical metadata variants of minecraft:log were as follows:
DV Description
0 Oak Log (up-down)
1 Spruce Log (up-down)
2 Birch Log (up-down)
3 Jungle Log (up-down)
4 Oak Log (east-west)
5 Spruce Log (east-west)
6 Birch Log (east-west)
7 Jungle Log (east-west)
8 Oak Log (north-south)
9 Spruce Log (north-south)
10 Birch Log (north-south)
11 Jungle Log (north-south)
12 Oak Wood (up-down)
13 Spruce Wood (up-down)
14 Birch Wood (up-down)
15 Jungle Wood (up-down)
The data values for minecraft:log2 were as follows:
DV Description
0 Acacia Log (up-down)
1 Dark Oak Log (up-down)
2-3 Inaccessible "boring" log blocks
4 Acacia Log (east-west)
5 Dark Oak Log (east-west)
6-7 Inaccessible "boring" log blocks
8 Acacia Log (north-south)
9 Dark Oak Log (north-south)
10-11 Inaccessible "boring" log blocks
12 Acacia Wood (up-down)
13 Dark Oak Wood (up-down)
14-15 Inaccessible "boring" wood blocks
minecraft:log2 with metadata values 2-3, 6-7, 10-11 and 14-15 have now been completely removed from the game.
The different variant block states and the axis=none block state for both the log and log2 IDs have been split up into their own IDs.
Prior to The Flattening, these blocks' numeral IDs were 17 and 162.
